The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Sunday, December 28, 2003 				 Indian Airlines prunes loss
																								New Delhi, Dec. 27 (PTI): Indian Airlines has reported a net loss of over Rs 196 crore in 2002-03, which was Rs 50 crore lower than the previous fiscal, and an eight per cent increase in its operating revenue.																								While there was an increase in the operating expenses by 5.41 per cent, the airline achieved an eight per cent increase in its operating revenue leading to reduction in operating loss by almost 39 per cent and net loss by over 20 per cent, as per the companys balance sheet adopted at its annual general meeting here.																								The reduction in the net loss was achieved through improved physical performance and strict cost control measures it had undertaken, an IA spokesman said.																								The airlines foreign exchange earnings amounted to Rs 1410 crore, which constituted about 35 per cent of the total operating revenue during the year, an ia spokesman said.																								On its physical performance, the carrier enhanced its revenue per tonne per kilometre by 12 per cent compared with the previous fiscal. 																								Indian Airlines recorded an improvement in its load factor by 2.7 per cent and increased its passengers carried figure by nine per cent. 
